  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the programme is to develop a treatment model for adolescents with Chronic Fatigue
      Syndrome. The program consists of 4 elements lasting for 12 months, psychoeducation
      reflecting the current knowledge about the disease, Heart Rate Variability Coherence
      Biofeedback, pacing and activity planning and some principles of cognitive behaviour therapy.
      The study is designed as a Single-Case study including 10- 15 participants.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
